    "recap_headline": "University of Houston Athletics",
    "recap_text": "LAWRENCE, Kansas \u2013\nThe Houston Baseball team dropped the series finale to Kansas, 8-4, on Sunday at Hoglund Ballpark.\nHouston's (12-11, 1-5 Big 12)\nJackson Baker\n(2-1) suffered the loss, surrendering the go-ahead run in the bottom of the eighth. Manning West (2-0) secured the win in relief, throwing the final 1.1 innings to claim the victory for Kansas (15-8, 4-2 Big 12).\nPLAYER HIGHLIGHTS\nTyler Cox\n: 3-5, 2 RBI, 2B\nCade Climie\n: 1-2, 2 R, 2 BB\nNOTABLES\nSenior\nTyler Cox\npicked up his fifth multi-hit game of the season.\nGAME SUMMARY\nHouston struck first as Cox slipped a double into right-center that allowed sophomore\nJustin Cherrington\nand senior\nCade Climie\nto score. Kansas evened the score in the third as a sacrifice fly and a double pushed a pair of runs across to make the score 2-2.\nThe Cougars reclaimed the lead as Cox earned his second RBI of the day with a groundout that allowed Climie to score in the fourth. The Jayhawks answered in the bottom of the inning as a bases-loaded single drove home a pair to give Kansas a 4-3 edge.\nA double-steal in the eighth tied the game as freshman\nPeyton Dickens\nscored, but Kansas claimed the lead for good with a solo homer and a three-run double in the bottom of the inning to earn an 8-4 victory.\nUP NEXT\nHouston returns home for a 6:30 p.m. Tuesday tilt against #2 Texas at Don Sanders Field at Darryl and Lori Schroeder Park.\nSUPPORT THE COUGARS\nFans can make a direct impact on the success of Houston Baseball by\nproviding NIL opportunities\nand by\njoining the Dugout Club\nwhich provides financial support directly to Houston Baseball for needs beyond its operating budget.\nSTAY CONNECTED\nFans can receive updates by following\n@UHCougarBB\non X, formerly known as Twitter, and catch up with the latest news and notes on the team by clicking LIKE on the team's Facebook page at\nHouston Cougar Baseball\n. Fans can also follow the team on Instagram at\n@uhcougarbb\n.\n\u2013 UHCougars.com \u2013",
